coalition. It's a question,
as King Abdullah has said,
Muslim troops on

00:43.410 --> 00:48.315 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the ground, not American troops.
And, by the
way, it is not a question of
going to war

00:48.348 --> 00:50.183 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
against a religion.

00:50.217 --> 00:56.056 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And we travel to
the Philippines,
where young girls are lured into
the sex trade

00:56.089 --> 00:57.658 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
online.

00:57.691 --> 01:04.631 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
All that and more on tonight's
"PBS NewsHour."

01:04.665 --> 01:07.501 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

01:07.534 --> 01:17.744 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The city of
Brussels began
three days of mourning today; 31
people were

01:17.778 --> 01:23.150 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
killed and 270 others wounded in
Tuesday's
suicide attacks.

01:23.183 --> 01:28.055 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Today, investigators kept up a
manhunt, as
the city tried to get back to
something like

01:28.088 --> 01:29.356 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
normal.

01:29.389 --> 01:31.491 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Malcolm Brabant reports from
Brussels.

01:31.525 --> 01:36.596 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: Hundreds
gathered in Brussels'
Place de la Bourse this morning
to remember

01:36.630 --> 01:40.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the victims of yesterday's twin
bombings with
a moment of silence.

01:40.434 --> 01:45.605 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WOMAN: Well, I think everyone
can agree that
this is a horrible, horrible,
horrible thing.

01:45.639 --> 01:48.308 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I think that's all there is left
to say about
it.

01:48.342 --> 01:52.646 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CAROLINE LEDENT, Brussels
Resident (through
translator): I think we had to
be here. I

01:52.679 --> 01:56.850 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
don't have the words to express
what I feel,
but it's true that we have been
used to see

01:56.883 --> 02:01.688 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
these attacks for a long time,
but when it
happens at home, you feel it in
a stronger

02:01.722 --> 02:03.490 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
way.

02:03.523 --> 02:06.426 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: Elsewhere in
the city, flags
at European Union buildings were
lowered to

02:06.460 --> 02:12.499 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
half-staff. European leaders
laid a wreath
at the metro station where one
of the bombers

02:12.532 --> 02:17.771 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
struck, and Belgium's king and
queen visited
with staff and emergency
responders at the

02:17.804 --> 02:23.410 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Brussels Airport, which
announced it will
remain closed at least another
day.

02:23.443 --> 02:27.981 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Many others in the Belgian
capital took pride
in returning to work and routine
as a sign

02:28.015 --> 02:29.950 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of strength in the face of
terror.

02:29.983 --> 02:34.154 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WOMAN: We all have to, because,
otherwise,
I think they will win. That's
what they want,

02:34.187 --> 02:38.091 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to paralyze our lives in Europe,
and we have
to go on with it.

02:38.125 --> 02:42.429 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WOMAN: We shouldn't be afraid. I
think the
most straight answer is to be
there, to continue

02:42.462 --> 02:46.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
our lives, to go to the
terraces, to drink
our coffee, to go to the cinema
and so on.

02:46.433 --> 02:51.304 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: But, as life
went on, so
did the search for answers.
Investigators

02:51.338 --> 02:55.409 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
now believe at least four
individuals were
involved in the attacks.

02:55.442 --> 03:00.480 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They say Ibrahim El Bakraoui and
another man
seen were the suicide bombers
who struck the

03:00.514 --> 03:06.553 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
departures concourse. That
second man, Najim
Laachraoui, allegedly also made
the suicide

03:06.586 --> 03:09.389 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
vests for the Paris bombings.

03:09.423 --> 03:14.594 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And it was El Bakraoui's
brother, Khalid,
who blew himself up on a subway
car near the

03:14.628 --> 03:20.033 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
European Union complex about an
hour later.
The third man, not yet
identified from the

03:20.067 --> 03:22.235 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
airport photo, is still being
sought.

03:22.269 --> 03:26.039 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FREDERIC VAN LEEUW, Belgian
Federal Prosecutor
(through translator): The third
suspect wearing

03:26.073 --> 03:31.178 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a light jacket and a hat is on
the run. He
put down a large bag, then left
before the

03:31.211 --> 03:36.083 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
explosion. It contained the
largest explosive
charge. Shortly after the
arrival of the bomb

03:36.116 --> 03:40.954 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
disposal unit, this bag blew up
because of
the highly unstable nature of
the explosives.

03:40.987 --> 03:42.756 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Fortunately, nobody was injured.

03:42.789 --> 03:47.094 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: Officials say
the two brothers
did have criminal records tied
to robbery

03:47.127 --> 03:53.967 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and carjacking, but it wasn't
until a March
15 raid on a Belgium apartment
rented by Khalid

03:54.000 --> 03:59.039 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
El Bakraoui that they became
suspects in the
ongoing terror probe.

03:59.072 --> 04:04.744 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That search also turned up
fingerprints belonging
to Salah Abdeslam, the top
suspect in November's

04:04.778 --> 04:11.351 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
terror attacks in Paris. He was
captured last
week. One of several raids since
yesterday's

04:11.384 --> 04:17.457 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
attacks turned up explosives and
chemicals
used to make bombs, as well as
Ibrahim El

04:17.491 --> 04:23.029 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Bakraoui's computer on which he
said he was
unsure what to do, hunted
everywhere, and

04:23.063 --> 04:24.898 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
no longer safe.

04:24.931 --> 04:29.970 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Today, Turkish President Recep
Tayyip Erdogan
said one of the attackers was
deported from

04:30.003 --> 04:31.872 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Turkey in June.

04:31.905 --> 04:35.642 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RECEP TAYYIP ERDOGAN, Turkish
President (through
translator): We informed the
Belgium Embassy

04:35.675 --> 04:41.815 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
